      {
        "id": "UgzVnBZlVxuLW6Z7Q9p4AaABAg.9Vb14bESlNd9Vbr1SXdBQX",
        "author": "@l0I0I0I0",
        "author_channel_id": "UCQOg6ujmK1wrjqnmDsADeGQ",
        "text": "@ThinkingandTinkering Yes not my specialty stacking turbines.  I've seen  however some of the more powerful professional drones have two blades stacked.  Guessing top turbine creates high pressure as a starting place for the second, which has a higher intake starting pressure for the second turbine, increasing output thrust.   I've seen vacuum chambers use three chambers going from low to lower pressure opposite goal but same principle.  It's all fluid Mechanic's.",
